Â¿quÃ© entendemos por identidad cultural? La identidad cultural se refiere a la forma en que una persona o grupo se identifica y se relaciona con una determinada cultura. La cultura se refiere al conjunto de conocimientos, creencias, valores, costumbres, tradiciones, arte y comportamientos que son compartidos y transmitidos por una sociedad o grupo de personas. A new coronavirus broke out in Wuhan City, Hubei Province in late 2019. It quickly spread to other parts of the world. Since late January 2020, people in China and more than ten countries in Asia, North America and Europe, have been confirmed to have contracted the virus.  Similar to what happened 17 years ago with the SARS outbreak, the Chinese Communist Party covered up information during the new epidemic. Many experts estimated that the actual infection cases and death toll are much higher than the numbers provided by the Chinese authorities.  With the lockdown of almost the entire Hubei Province and continued tight control and censorship of real information, many Chinese people are now left in a desperate situation.  In this podcast, we hope to provide useful information to you and that you can protect yourself and your family in the face of the epidemic.  Part 1: Coronavirus Epidemic Updates Due to the quick spread of the coronavirus, Wuhan authorities announced at 2 a.m. on January 24 that they were locking down the entire city and banning all modes of transportation starting at 10 a.m. that day. A local newspaper reported, â€œThere is still an eight-hour window for people to choose to leave the city if they wish to.â€  According to news circulated on WeChat, a popular Chinese social media platform, in the 22 days since the discovery of the virus, many people have flown out of Wuhan, including 43,000 to Haikou, 27,000 to Sanya, 5,600 to Bozhe, 59,000 to Beijing, 70,000 to Shanghai, 49,000 to Guangzhou, 37,000 to Shenzhen, 47,000 to Chengdu, and 22,000 to Chongqing. The data reportedly came from airline companies.  Only two days after the lockdown, thirty provinces in China reported infection cases and declared a â€œgrade 1 public health emergency.â€ Outside of China, virus patients have also been reported in Hong Kong, Macao, Singapore, Taiwan, Thailand, Vietnam, Malaysia, Nepal, Japan, the UK, the US, Canada, France and Australia.  The Independent, a prominent UK newspaper, published an article titled â€œCoronavirus reaches Europe as UK â€˜hunts for 2,000 passengers who recently arrived from Wuhanâ€™â€ on January 24. The report said that UK public health officials have been working with airlines to trace some 2,000 people who had entered the country from Wuhan in the last 14 days. According to the report, â€œProfessor Paul Cosford, medical director at Public Health England, has said it is still 'early days' for the virus but admitted that it is 'highly likely' that cases of the new strain of coronavirus will be seen in the UK, after tests on more than a dozen people.â€  Taiwan has confirmed four cases. The government suggested that its citizens do not visit Wuhan or the rest of Hubei Province. Taiwan also announced on January 24 that visitors from China, Hong Kong, and Macao must fill out a health survey at customs. In addition, Taiwan also banned local residents from traveling to China for tourism.
